<section id="neutron-welcome-screen">
	<h1>Hello Neutron!</h1>

	<p>Welcome to Neutron Atomic Design Tool. These pages are automatically generated as a static site.</p>

	<h2>How to use Neutron?</h2>

	<p>To use Neutron is quite simple. At the left/right corner you may see a button, the <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="neutron-svg-inline"><use class="neutron-svg-icon" xlink:href="#neutron-logo"></use></svg> button. To activate Neutron Navigation, you just need to press the key <strong>n</strong> or click/touch on this button.</p>

	<p>The Neutron navigation bar consists in:</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="neutron-svg-inline">
				<use class="neutron-svg-icon" xlink:href="#neutron-search"></use>
			</svg>
			Search Button - opens the search input and find your desired pattern. Shortcut: <strong>f</strong>
		</li>
		<li>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="neutron-svg-inline">
				<use class="neutron-svg-icon" xlink:href="#neutron-code-frame"></use>
			</svg>
			Code Frame Button - opens a frame below containing your HTML and Handlebars markup, including the pattern documentation. It also shows the dependencies and reverse dependencies list. Shortcut: <strong>c</strong>
		</li>
		<li>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="neutron-svg-inline">
				<use class="neutron-svg-icon" xlink:href="#neutron-qr-code"></use>
			</svg>
			QR Code Button - opens a lightbox with QR Code to easily load it in your mobile device. Shortcut: <strong>q</strong>
		</li>
		<li>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 1792 1792" class="neutron-svg-inline">
				<use class="neutron-svg-icon" xlink:href="#neutron-info"></use>
			</svg>
			Settings Button - opens a lightbox with basic information and settings. Shortcut: <strong>s</strong>
		</li>
		<li>Main menu including all patterns: Atoms, Molecules, Organisms, Templates, Pages</li>
	</ul>

	<p><cite>Neutron is attached by default in all generated pages as a standalone script, it means you must have Javascript enabled by default.</cite></p>
</section>
